      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHEER ME (1) was far from disgraced when midfield from the back row last time out and was good when runner-up here prior. Showed gate speed there so can be prominent from the ace draw. That could see her hard to catch. RYKER (4) started a hot favourite last start but manners let him down. Had been racing consistently with a string of top-four finishes prior, placing over this distance the last time he raced here. Big chance if he gets it right. THE PRIVATE DEAL (3) broke in his first outing for this yard last start but was fourth at Melton prior. Draws well so is worth another chance. Always B Miki filly ALWAYSTHEWILDEST (2) is at the track for the first time. Placed in her last two trials and should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position so anticipating a good start to her career.",
